10 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 37A O.S. 2021, Section 3-123, as
11 amended by Section 3, Chapter 94, O.S.L. 2023 (37A O.S. Supp. 2025,
12 Section 3-123), is amended to read as follows:
13 Section 3-123. A. It shall be unlawful for any person
14 privileged to sell alcoholic beverages to wholesalers, beer
15 distributors or retailers:
16 1. To discriminate, directly or indirectly, in price between
17 one wine and spirits wholesaler and another wine and spirits
18 wholesaler, when that manufacturer has not designated a single wine
19 and spirits wholesaler, or between one retailer and another retailer
20 purchasing alcoholic beverages bearing the same brand or trade name
21 and of like age and quality, unless otherwise provided by law; or
22 2. To grant, directly or indirectly, any discount, rebate, free
23 goods, allowance or other inducement.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1946 SFLR Page 13
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. The ABLE Commission is hereby authorized to promulgate rules
2 which are necessary to carry out the purpose of this section and to
3 prevent its circumvention by offering or giving of any rebate,
4 allowance, free goods, discount or any other thing or service of
5 value; provided, the posting or invoicing of charges per order for
6 processing minimum orders or per case for the handling or repacking
7 of goods by wine and spirits wholesalers and beer distributors for
8 sales in less than full case lots shall not constitute a violation
9 of this section.
10 C. For the violation of any provision of this section or of any
11 rule duly promulgated under this section, the ABLE Commission may
12 issue a written warning, fine, suspend or revoke a license as
13 follows:
14 1. For a first offense, a written warning which may be
15 accompanied by a fine not to exceed Five Thousand Dollars
16 ($5,000.00);
17 2. For a second offense, not exceeding ten (10) days’
18 suspension of license; and
19 3. For a third offense, the ABLE Commission shall revoke the
20 license.
21 Provided, however, prior to suspending or revoking a license,
22 the ABLE Commission shall first provide written notice to a licensee
23 of the violation and a period of ninety (90) days following such
24 notice to cure or remedy such violation. For purposes of this
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1946 SFLR Page 14
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 sect ion, a “second offense” and “third offense” shall mean
2 violations that are related to or arising out of and occurring
3 within twelve (12) months of the “first offense”.
